{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"'Theme and variations' is one of those forms that"},{"time":3000,"text":"require a certain kind of intellectual activity,"},{"time":8000,"text":"because you are always comparing the variation"},{"time":11000,"text":"with the theme that you hold in your mind."},{"time":14000,"text":"You might say that the theme is nature"},{"time":18000,"text":"and everything that follows is a variation on the subject."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"I was asked, I guess about six years ago,"},{"time":36000,"text":"to do a series of paintings"},{"time":41000,"text":"that in some way would celebrate the birth of Piero della Francesca."},{"time":48000,"text":"And it was very difficult for me to imagine"},{"time":52000,"text":"how to paint pictures that were based on Piero"},{"time":61000,"text":"until I realized that I could look at Piero as nature --"},{"time":68000,"text":"that I would have the same attitude towards looking at Piero della Francesca"},{"time":75000,"text":"as I would if I were looking out a window at a tree."},{"time":78000,"text":"And that was enormously liberating to me."},{"time":81000,"text":"Perhaps it's not a very insightful observation,"},{"time":85000,"text":"but that really started me on a path to be able to do a kind of theme and variations"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"based on a work by Piero,"},{"time":95000,"text":"in this case that remarkable painting that's in the Uffizi, \"The Duke of Montefeltro,\""},{"time":102000,"text":"who faces his consort, Battista."},{"time":107000,"text":"Once I realized that I could take some liberties with the subject,"},{"time":111000,"text":"I did the following series of drawings."},{"time":115000,"text":"That's the real Piero della Francesca --"},{"time":120000,"text":"one of the greatest portraits in human history."},{"time":125000,"text":"And these, I'll just show these without comment."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's just a series of variations on the head of the Duke of Montefeltro,"},{"time":135000,"text":"who's a great, great figure in the Renaissance,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and probably the basis for Machiavelli's \"The Prince.\""},{"time":141000,"text":"He apparently lost an eye in battle,"},{"time":144000,"text":"which is why he is always shown in profile."},{"time":147000,"text":"And this is Battista."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"And then I decided I could move them around a little bit --"},{"time":158000,"text":"so that for the first time in history, they're facing the same direction."},{"time":161000,"text":"Whoops! Passed each other."},{"time":168000,"text":"And then a visitor from another painting by Piero,"},{"time":171000,"text":"this is from \"The Resurrection of Christ\" --"},{"time":174000,"text":"as though the cast had just gotten of the set to have a chat."},{"time":179000,"text":"And now, four large panels:"},{"time":182000,"text":"this is upper left;"},{"time":184000,"text":"upper right;"},{"time":188000,"text":"lower left;"},{"time":191000,"text":"lower right."},{"time":193000,"text":"Incidentally, I've never understood the conflict between abstraction and naturalism."},{"time":200000,"text":"Since all paintings are inherently abstract to begin with"},{"time":204000,"text":"there doesn't seem to be an argument there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"On another subject --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"I was driving in the country one day with my wife,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and I saw this sign,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and I said, \"That is a fabulous piece of design.\""},{"time":222000,"text":"And she said, \"What are you talking about?\""},{"time":225000,"text":"I said, \"Well, it's so persuasive,"},{"time":227000,"text":"because the purpose of that sign is to get you into the garage,"},{"time":232000,"text":"and since most people are so suspicious of garages,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and know that they're going to be ripped off,"},{"time":240000,"text":"they use the word 'reliable.'"},{"time":243000,"text":"But everybody says they're reliable."},{"time":245000,"text":"But, reliable Dutchman\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"\"Fantastic!\""},{"time":252000,"text":"Because as soon as you hear the word Dutchman --"},{"time":255000,"text":"which is an archaic word, nobody calls Dutch people \"Dutchmen\" anymore --"},{"time":258000,"text":"but as soon as you hear Dutchman,"},{"time":260000,"text":"you get this picture of the kid with his finger in the dike,"},{"time":263000,"text":"preventing the thing from falling and flooding Holland, and so on."},{"time":266000,"text":"And so the entire issue is detoxified by the use of \"Dutchman.\""},{"time":273000,"text":"Now, if you think I'm exaggerating at all in this,"},{"time":276000,"text":"all you have to do is substitute something else, like \"Indonesian.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"Or even \"French.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"Now, \"Swiss\" works, but you know it's going to cost a lot of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"I'm going to take you quickly through the actual process of doing a poster."},{"time":309000,"text":"I do a lot of work for the School of Visual Arts, where I teach,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and the director of this school -- a remarkable man named Silas Rhodes --"},{"time":315000,"text":"often gives you a piece of text and he says, \"Do something with this.\""},{"time":320000,"text":"And so he did."},{"time":322000,"text":"And this was the text -- \"In words as fashion the same rule will hold/"},{"time":325000,"text":"Alike fantastic if too new or old/"},{"time":326000,"text":"Be not the first by whom the new are tried/"},{"time":330000,"text":"Nor yet the last to lay the old aside.\""},{"time":333000,"text":"I could make nothing of that."},{"time":335000,"text":"And I really struggled with this one."},{"time":337000,"text":"And the first thing I did, which was sort of in the absence of another idea,"},{"time":340000,"text":"was say I'll sort of write it out and make some words big,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and I'll have some kind of design on the back somehow,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and I was hoping -- as one often does -- to stumble into something."},{"time":351000,"text":"So I took another crack at it --"},{"time":354000,"text":"you've got to keep it moving --"},{"time":356000,"text":"and I Xeroxed some words on pieces of colored paper"},{"time":358000,"text":"and I pasted them down on an ugly board."},{"time":361000,"text":"I thought that something would come out of it,"},{"time":364000,"text":"like \"Words rule fantastic new old first last Pope\""},{"time":367000,"text":"because it's by Alexander Pope,"},{"time":370000,"text":"but I sort of made a mess out of it,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and then I thought I'd repeat it in some way so it was legible."},{"time":374000,"text":"So, it was going nowhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"Sometimes, in the middle of a resistant problem,"},{"time":381000,"text":"I write down things that I know about it."},{"time":384000,"text":"But you can see the beginning of an idea there,"},{"time":386000,"text":"because you can see the word \"new\" emerging from the \"old.\""},{"time":389000,"text":"That's what happens."},{"time":391000,"text":"There's a relationship between the old and the new;"},{"time":394000,"text":"the new emerges from the context of the old."},{"time":396000,"text":"And then I did some variations of it,"},{"time":398000,"text":"but it still wasn't coalescing graphically at all."},{"time":402000,"text":"I had this other version which had something interesting about it"},{"time":405000,"text":"in terms of being able to put it together in your mind from clues."},{"time":411000,"text":"The W was clearly a W, the N was clearly an N,"},{"time":414000,"text":"even though they were very fragmentary"},{"time":418000,"text":"and there wasn't a lot of information in it."},{"time":420000,"text":"Then I got the words \"new\" and \"old\""},{"time":422000,"text":"and now I had regressed back to a point where there seemed to be no return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"I was really desperate at this point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"And so, I do something I'm truthfully ashamed of,"},{"time":436000,"text":"which is that I took two drawings I had made for another purpose"},{"time":440000,"text":"and I put them together."},{"time":445000,"text":"It says \"dreams\" at the top."},{"time":448000,"text":"And I was going to do a thing, I say, \"Well, change the copy."},{"time":451000,"text":"Let it say something about dreams, and come to SVA"},{"time":455000,"text":"and you'll sort of fulfill your dreams.\""},{"time":457000,"text":"But, to my credit,"},{"time":459000,"text":"I was so embarrassed about doing that"},{"time":462000,"text":"that I never submitted this sketch."},{"time":466000,"text":"And, finally, I arrived at the following solution."},{"time":471000,"text":"Now, it doesn't look terribly interesting,"},{"time":475000,"text":"but it does have something"},{"time":478000,"text":"that distinguishes it from a lot of other posters."},{"time":484000,"text":"For one thing, it transgresses the idea of what a poster's supposed to be,"},{"time":488000,"text":"which is to be understood and seen immediately, and not explained."},{"time":496000,"text":"I remember hearing all of you in the graphic arts --"},{"time":499000,"text":"\"If you have to explain it, it ain't working.\""},{"time":502000,"text":"And one day I woke up and I said, \"Well, suppose that's not true?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"So here's what it says in my explanation at the bottom left."},{"time":517000,"text":"It says, \"Thoughts: This poem is impossible."},{"time":523000,"text":"Silas usually has a better touch with his choice of quotations."},{"time":527000,"text":"This one generates no imagery at all.\""},{"time":529000,"text":"I am now exposing myself to my audience, right?"},{"time":532000,"text":"Which is something you never want to do professionally."},{"time":535000,"text":"\"Maybe the words can make the image without anything else happening."},{"time":539000,"text":"What's the heart of this poem?"},{"time":541000,"text":"Don't be trendy if you want to be serious."},{"time":543000,"text":"Is doing the poster this way trendy in itself?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"I guess one could reduce the idea further"},{"time":548000,"text":"by suggesting that the new emerges behind and through the old,"},{"time":552000,"text":"like this.\""},{"time":554000,"text":"And then I show you a little drawing --"},{"time":556000,"text":"you see, you remember that old thing I discarded?"},{"time":559000,"text":"Well, I found a way to use it."},{"time":561000,"text":"So, there's that little alternative over there,"},{"time":564000,"text":"and I say, \"Not bad,\" -- criticizing myself --"},{"time":568000,"text":"\"but more didactic than visual."},{"time":571000,"text":"Maybe what wants to be said is that old and the new are locked in a dialectical embrace,"},{"time":574000,"text":"a kind of dance where each defines the other.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"And then more self-questioning -- \"Am I being simple-minded?"},{"time":580000,"text":"Is this the kind of simple that looks obvious, or the kind that looks profound?"},{"time":584000,"text":"There's a significant difference."},{"time":586000,"text":"This could be embarrassing."},{"time":588000,"text":"Actually, I realize fear of embarrassment drives me as much as any ambition."},{"time":592000,"text":"Do you think this sort of thing could really attract a student to the school?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603000,"text":"Well, I think there are two fresh things here -- two fresh things."},{"time":608000,"text":"One is the sort of willingness to expose myself to a critical audience,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and not to suggest that I am confident about what I'm doing."},{"time":621000,"text":"And as you know, you have to have a front."},{"time":625000,"text":"I mean -- you've got to be confident;"},{"time":627000,"text":"if you don't believe in your work, who else is going to believe in it?"},{"time":630000,"text":"So that's one thing,"},{"time":632000,"text":"to introduce the idea of doubt into graphics."},{"time":637000,"text":"That can be a big contribution."},{"time":639000,"text":"The other thing is to actually give you two solutions for the price of one;"},{"time":643000,"text":"you get the big one"},{"time":646000,"text":"and if you don't like that, how about the little one?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"And that too is a relatively new idea."},{"time":654000,"text":"And here's just a series of experiments"},{"time":657000,"text":"where I ask the question of -- does a poster have to be square?"},{"time":662000,"text":"Now, this is a little illusion."},{"time":665000,"text":"That poster is not folded."},{"time":667000,"text":"It's not folded, that's a photograph"},{"time":670000,"text":"and it's cut on the diagonal."},{"time":673000,"text":"Same cheap trick in the upper left-hand corner."},{"time":678000,"text":"And here,"},{"time":680000,"text":"a very peculiar poster because,"},{"time":682000,"text":"simply because of using the isometric perspective in the computer,"},{"time":687000,"text":"it won't sit still in the space."},{"time":690000,"text":"At times, it seems to be wider at the back than the front,"},{"time":693000,"text":"and then it shifts."},{"time":695000,"text":"And if you sit here long enough, it'll float off the page into the audience."},{"time":700000,"text":"But, we don't have time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"And then an experiment --"},{"time":705000,"text":"a little bit about the nature of perspective,"},{"time":708000,"text":"where the outside shape is determined by the peculiarity of perspective,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but the shape of the bottle -- which is identical to the outside shape --"},{"time":716000,"text":"is seen frontally."},{"time":718000,"text":"And another piece for the art directors' club"},{"time":722000,"text":"is \"Anna Rees\" casting long shadows."},{"time":726000,"text":"This is another poster from the School of Visual Arts."},{"time":729000,"text":"There were 10 artists invited to participate in it,"},{"time":734000,"text":"and it was one of those things where it was extremely competitive"},{"time":736000,"text":"and I didn't want to be embarrassed,"},{"time":738000,"text":"so I worked very hard on this."},{"time":741000,"text":"The idea was -- and it was a brilliant idea --"},{"time":743000,"text":"was to have 10 posters distributed throughout the city's subway system"},{"time":747000,"text":"so every time you got on the subway you'd be passing a different poster,"},{"time":751000,"text":"all of which had a different idea of what art is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"But I was absolutely stuck on the idea of \"art is\""},{"time":761000,"text":"and trying to determine what art was."},{"time":765000,"text":"But then I gave up and I said, \"Well, art is whatever.\""},{"time":769000,"text":"And as soon as I said that,"},{"time":771000,"text":"I discovered that the word \"hat\" was hidden in the word \"whatever,\""},{"time":774000,"text":"and that led me to the inevitable conclusion."},{"time":777000,"text":"But then again, it's on my list of didactic posters."},{"time":781000,"text":"My intent is to have a literary accompaniment that explains the poster,"},{"time":785000,"text":"in case you don't get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"Now this says, \"Note to the viewer:"},{"time":792000,"text":"I thought I might use a visual cliche of our time -- Magritte's everyman --"},{"time":795000,"text":"to express the idea that art is mystery, continuity and history."},{"time":799000,"text":"I'm also convinced that, in an age of computer manipulation,"},{"time":802000,"text":"surrealism has become banal,"},{"time":805000,"text":"a shadow of its former self."},{"time":807000,"text":"The phrase 'Art is whatever'"},{"time":809000,"text":"expresses the current inclusiveness that surrounds art-making --"},{"time":812000,"text":"a sort of 'it ain't what you do, it's the way that you do it' notion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"The shadow of Magritte falls across the central part of the poster"},{"time":819000,"text":"a poetic event that occurs as the shadow man isolates the word 'hat,'"},{"time":824000,"text":"hidden in the word 'whatever.'"},{"time":826000,"text":"The four hats shown in the poster suggests how art might be defined:"},{"time":829000,"text":"as a thing itself, the worth of the thing, the shadow of the thing,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and the shape of the thing."},{"time":835000,"text":"Whatever.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":837000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":838000,"text":"OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"And the one that I did not submit,"},{"time":847000,"text":"which I still like,"},{"time":849000,"text":"I wanted to use the same phrase."},{"time":851000,"text":"There were wonderful experiments by Bruno Munari"},{"time":857000,"text":"on letterforms some years ago --"},{"time":859000,"text":"sort of, see how far you could go and still be able to read them."},{"time":861000,"text":"And that idea stuck in my head."},{"time":863000,"text":"But then I took the pieces that I had taken off and put them at the bottom."},{"time":868000,"text":"And, of course those are the remains, and they're so labeled."},{"time":873000,"text":"But what really happens is that you read it as:"},{"time":876000,"text":"\"Art is whatever remains.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}